snippet.textDisplay: Beautifully done. Constructive opinions are great but there is lot of comparison between Rohail vs Strings vs Others. Of course they are all different thinkers, hence their music style is different. Lets just all agree that no matter what Coke Studio provides us with exceptional music, way better than what comes out of Bollywood and most of the other musicians who are trying to make one hit wonders. The one hit wonders will be played and forgotten, CS will forever live strong. Long live Coke Studio be it CS Pakistan or CS India. Absolutely beautiful stuff.

snippet.textDisplay:
Brilliant composition but as a listener i think some time too much experiments ruins things, Damia Farooq started it well, with nice soft classical touch, that should remained up to half of the song along with basit, and only One transition from soft rhythm to a westernized one after the first half sung by both singers would sound great.
With current arrangements, as a listener, one just start enjoying the first 1 min of classical and soft part, and suddenly rhythm changes, and when a listener shift to that part, yet again, rhythm changes and so as at the end once again. That's disturbing the flow and feelings of the song.
P.S: I am not a pro, these are my thoughts the way i felt.
